Males
. Carapace brown-black with narrow yellow median band (
Figure 1C
); lateral light bands brown, darker than median band, and slightly narrower than dark marginal bands; clypeus light brown, lighter than head flanks (
Figure 1B
). Abdomen similar colour to carapace, with light brown median heart mark. Legs yellow without annulations. Femora basally dark. Metatarsi I with a few scattered small pores (
Figure 2J
). Tarsi I apically dark (
Figure 1E,F
). Chelicerae of similar colour to carapace, with longitudinal stripes of similar colour as clypeus. Pedipalps dark brown; patellae slightly lighter than other segments. Palea with smoothly rounded ridge (
Figure 3B,C
); terminal apophysis rounded (
Figure 3A,C,D
), with distinctly separated mesal portion.

Females
. Carapace brown with wide yellow median band and distinct cephalic spot (
Figure 1A
); lateral light bands twice as wide as marginal dark bands. Abdomen with distinct light heart mark and five pairs of light median spots. Anterior spots separated by heart mark, the posterior spots fused. Legs with dark annulations (
Figure 1A
). Epigyne with wide median septum, that covers the entire cavity and distinct apical pockets (
Figures 3
G–I; 4A,H); median septum variable in size and shape, its median part without longitudinal groove (
Figure 4E
); apical pockets widely separated.
